Column-normalizing plots (as has been done, e.g., for those in Figs. 13, 14) is a powerful and well established technique for exploring collisional effects in solar-wind plasma. It represents a refinement of the method used in some of the earliest studies of collisional relaxation (e.g., Feldman et al. 1974a; Neugebauer 1976), in which data were divided into logarithmically uniform Nc\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
