				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\sim \beta _{\mathrm {p}}^{-1/2}$$\end{document} (Squire et al. 2016). Beyond this limit, the pressure anisotropy associated with the wave fluctuations exceeds the parallel-firehose limit and destroys the restoring force associated with the magnetic tension, which destabilizes the wave. Numerical simulations confirm signatures of this instability, which are currently also being sought in solar-wind observations under high-βp\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
